title: CSU’s Culbert named MW Player of the Week
text:
CSU’s Culbert named MW Player of the Week After recording first quadruple-double in school history, Culbert earns MW honor. Join the Conversation Kevin Lytle, kevinlytle@coloradoan.com 11:53 a.m. MDT October 19, 2015 CSU’s Adrianna Culbert, shown in a match earlier this season, recorded a triple-double and the school’s first quadruple-double last week. (Photo: Austin Humphreys/The Coloradoan) CONNECT 6 TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
After her record-setting performance last week, CSU senior Adrianna Culbert has been named the Mountain West defensive Player of the Week. 
The setter/opposite hitter recorded 12 kills, 18 assists and 10 digs for her CSU and Mountain West record fifth triple-double of the season in a sweep of Wyoming on Tuesday. 
She topped herself in a sweep of San Jose State on Saturday. She had 10 kills, 20 assists, 13 digs and 10 blocks for the first quadruple-double in CSU and Mountain West history. 
It’s the second MW weekly award of the season for Culbert. She was named the offensive player of the week earlier this season. 
Also on Monday, CSU moved up one spot to No. 20 in the AVCA coaches poll. The Rams have won nine matches in a row. 
The Rams (15-3, 8-0 MW) play at Boise State (14-6, 6-2 MW) at 7 p.m. Thursday. Read or Share this story: http://noconow.co/1LGzPai TOP VIDEOS
